[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1047},["ShallowReactive",2],{"writings/what-is-machine-learning":3},{"id":4,"title":5,"body":6,"cover":1031,"description":1032,"extension":1033,"head":1031,"meta":1034,"navigation":1035,"ogImage":1031,"path":1036,"publishedAt":1037,"readingTime":1038,"robots":1031,"schemaOrg":1031,"seo":1039,"sitemap":1040,"slug":1041,"stem":1042,"tags":1043,"__hash__":1046},"writings/writings/what-is-machine-learning.md","What is Machine Learning?",{"type":7,"value":8,"toc":1021},"minimark",[9,14,18,21,50,54,57,192,198,201,205,208,256,259,263,266,435,439,442,446,453,774,944,1007,1011,1014,1018],[10,11,13],"h2",{"id":12},"_1-introduction","1 - Introduction",[15,16,17],"p",{},"Machine Learning (ML) is a key discipline in artificial intelligence (AI), enabling systems to learn from data to make predictions or discover patterns. It is the driving force behind many modern innovations, from personalised recommendations to autonomous vehicles.",[15,19,20],{},"In this article, we will cover:",[22,23,24,32,38,44],"ol",{},[25,26,27,31],"li",{},[28,29,30],"strong",{},"The types of Machine Learning",", to understand the different approaches.",[25,33,34,37],{},[28,35,36],{},"Three considerations for choosing a supervised learning model",", one of the most common ML paradigms.",[25,39,40,43],{},[28,41,42],{},"The typical ML workflow",", exploring the essential steps for developing a model.",[25,45,46,49],{},[28,47,48],{},"Model evaluation through the R² score",", an important metric for regression problems.",[10,51,53],{"id":52},"_2-the-types-of-machine-learning","2 - The Types of Machine Learning",[15,55,56],{},"To start, it is important to understand the three main categories of machine learning:",[22,58,59,160,186],{},[25,60,61,64,65,112,113,144,145],{},[28,62,63],{},"Supervised Learning"," This type of learning relies on labeled data, where the model learns to map inputs ",[66,67,70,92],"span",{"className":68},[69],"katex",[66,71,74],{"className":72},[73],"katex-mathml",[75,76,78],"math",{"xmlns":77},"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML",[79,80,81,88],"semantics",{},[82,83,84],"mrow",{},[85,86,87],"mi",{},"X",[89,90,87],"annotation",{"encoding":91},"application/x-tex",[66,93,97],{"className":94,"ariaHidden":96},[95],"katex-html","true",[66,98,101,106],{"className":99},[100],"base",[66,102],{"className":103,"style":105},[104],"strut","height:0.6833em;",[66,107,87],{"className":108,"style":111},[109,110],"mord","mathnormal","margin-right:0.07847em;"," to outputs ",[66,114,116,130],{"className":115},[69],[66,117,119],{"className":118},[73],[75,120,121],{"xmlns":77},[79,122,123,128],{},[82,124,125],{},[85,126,127],{},"y",[89,129,127],{"encoding":91},[66,131,133],{"className":132,"ariaHidden":96},[95],[66,134,136,140],{"className":135},[100],[66,137],{"className":138,"style":139},[104],"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;",[66,141,127],{"className":142,"style":143},[109,110],"margin-right:0.03588em;",". Common tasks include:",[146,147,148,154],"ul",{},[25,149,150,153],{},[28,151,152],{},"Classification",": Assigning data to categories (e.g., spam detection).",[25,155,156,159],{},[28,157,158],{},"Regression",": Predicting continuous values (e.g., house price estimation).",[25,161,162,165,166],{},[28,163,164],{},"Unsupervised Learning"," In this case, no labels are provided, and the goal is to find structures or patterns. Common tasks include:",[146,167,168,174,180],{},[25,169,170,173],{},[28,171,172],{},"Clustering",": Grouping similar data points (e.g., customer segmentation).",[25,175,176,179],{},[28,177,178],{},"Dimensionality Reduction",": Simplifying data while retaining key information (e.g., PCA).",[25,181,182,185],{},[28,183,184],{},"Anomaly Detection",": Identifying unusual data points (e.g., fraud detection).",[25,187,188,191],{},[28,189,190],{},"Reinforcement Learning"," This learning type involves an agent interacting with an environment. The agent learns by trial and error to maximize cumulative rewards, as seen in robotics and gaming.",[193,194],"prose-img",{"caption":195,"label":196,"src":197},"The different types of machine learning models","ML Model Types","/writings/what-is-machine-learning/types.png",[15,199,200],{},"With this overview of ML types, let's now focus on supervised learning, the most widely used approach, and explore how to choose the right model.",[10,202,204],{"id":203},"_3-three-considerations-for-choosing-a-supervised-learning-model","3 - Three Considerations for Choosing a Supervised Learning Model",[15,206,207],{},"Selecting the right supervised learning model is critical and depends on several factors:",[22,209,210,226,241],{},[25,211,212,215],{},[28,213,214],{},"Problem Type",[146,216,217,220],{},[25,218,219],{},"Is it a regression or classification problem?",[25,221,222,225],{},[28,223,224],{},"Key Point",": Determine if the target variable is continuous or discrete.",[25,227,228,231],{},[28,229,230],{},"Problem Complexity",[146,232,233,236],{},[25,234,235],{},"Is the relationship between input features and the target variable linear or nonlinear?",[25,237,238,240],{},[28,239,224],{},": Understand whether the data allows for easy predictions or requires more complex models.",[25,242,243,246],{},[28,244,245],{},"Algorithmic Approach",[146,247,248,251],{},[25,249,250],{},"Should you choose a feature-based or similarity-based model?",[25,252,253,255],{},[28,254,224],{},": The choice of the model (e.g., linear regressions vs k-NN) depends on the dataset's size and complexity.",[15,257,258],{},"Once the model type is defined, the next step is to delve into the full workflow of developing an ML model.",[10,260,262],{"id":261},"_4-the-typical-workflow-in-machine-learning","4 - The Typical Workflow in Machine Learning",[15,264,265],{},"A machine learning project generally follows these steps:",[22,267,268,281,299],{},[25,269,270,273],{},[28,271,272],{},"Data Preparation",[146,274,275,278],{},[25,276,277],{},"Splitting data into training and testing sets.",[25,279,280],{},"Preprocessing: scaling, handling missing values, etc.",[25,282,283,286],{},[28,284,285],{},"Model Training",[146,287,288,296],{},[25,289,290,291,295],{},"Fitting the model on training data: ",[292,293,294],"code",{},"model.fit(X, y)",".",[25,297,298],{},"Optimising parameters and hyperparameters.",[25,300,301,304],{},[28,302,303],{},"Prediction and Evaluation",[146,305,306,312],{},[25,307,308,309,295],{},"Making predictions on unseen data: ",[292,310,311],{},"model.predict(X)",[25,313,314,315,405,406,434],{},"Comparing predictions (",[66,316,318,339],{"className":317},[69],[66,319,321],{"className":320},[73],[75,322,323],{"xmlns":77},[79,324,325,336],{},[82,326,327],{},[328,329,330,332],"mover",{"accent":96},[85,331,127],{},[333,334,335],"mo",{},"^",[89,337,338],{"encoding":91},"\\hat{y}",[66,340,342],{"className":341,"ariaHidden":96},[95],[66,343,345,349],{"className":344},[100],[66,346],{"className":347,"style":348},[104],"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;",[66,350,353],{"className":351},[109,352],"accent",[66,354,358,396],{"className":355},[356,357],"vlist-t","vlist-t2",[66,359,362,391],{"className":360},[361],"vlist-r",[66,363,367,378],{"className":364,"style":366},[365],"vlist","height:0.6944em;",[66,368,370,375],{"style":369},"top:-3em;",[66,371],{"className":372,"style":374},[373],"pstrut","height:3em;",[66,376,127],{"className":377,"style":143},[109,110],[66,379,380,383],{"style":369},[66,381],{"className":382,"style":374},[373],[66,384,388],{"className":385,"style":387},[386],"accent-body","left:-0.1944em;",[66,389,335],{"className":390},[109],[66,392,395],{"className":393},[394],"vlist-s","​",[66,397,399],{"className":398},[361],[66,400,403],{"className":401,"style":402},[365],"height:0.1944em;",[66,404],{},") with actual values (",[66,407,409,422],{"className":408},[69],[66,410,412],{"className":411},[73],[75,413,414],{"xmlns":77},[79,415,416,420],{},[82,417,418],{},[85,419,127],{},[89,421,127],{"encoding":91},[66,423,425],{"class